HTML - Hyper text markup language

- To create a web pages
- Not a Programming language
- Its a markup language
- Every website starts with HTML

1. Heading - h1 to h6

2. paragraph - p

3. hr

4. br

5. Text formating -b or strong, i, u, mark, sub and sup........

6. Anchor Tag - a

7. Image tag - img

8. list - order list and unorder list

9. Tables - tr, th and td

10. Forms - input and label

11. Media elements - Audio and video

12. Sematic tags - header, footer, section, nav and main

13. Division tag - div

CSS - Cascading Style Sheet

1. Types of css
   i - Inline
   ii - Internal
   iii - External

inline > internal > external

2. CSS Synatax
   selector {
   property: value;
   }

3. types of selector
   i - element selector - (p), (h3)
   ii - class selector (.) - multiple type can use the same class name because its number of time
   iii - id selector (#) - only one time can use the same id name because its unique
   iv - universal selector (\*) - for entire site it will act
   v - group selector -

4. Colors and background
   color: red; ( font color )
   background-color: olive;
   background-image: url(./Assets/Ajith\ image.jpg);
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
   background-size: cover;
   background-position: center;

5. Text Styling
   font-family: Impact, Haettenschweiler, 'Arial Narrow Bold', sans-serif;
   font-size: 30px;
   text-align: center;
   text-transform: uppercase;
   text-decoration: line-through;
   font-weight: bold;
   line-height: 1;
   letter-spacing: 1px;

6. Box modeling
   margin
   border
   padding
   content

7. Flex
   direction - row, row-reverse, column, column-reverse
   justify-content (X) - start, center, end, space-around, space-evenly, space-between
   align-items (Y) - start, center, end
   flex-wrap - no-wrap, wrap, wrap-reverse
